---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Terms of Service | Zig Index";
const pageDescription = "Terms of Service for Zig Index - Community guidelines and usage terms for the Zig package registry.";
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Terms of Service</h1>
      
      <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-6">
        <strong>Last updated:</strong> {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'long', day: 'numeric', year: 'numeric' })}
      </p>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing and using Zig Index ("the Service"), you accept and agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use the Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Description of Service</h2>
        <p>
          Zig Index is a community-driven registry that helps developers discover Zig programming language packages and applications. The Service provides:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>A curated directory of Zig packages and applications</li>
          <li>Links to GitHub repositories and documentation</li>
          <li>Search and filtering capabilities</li>
          <li>Repository statistics and information</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Zig Index does not host any package code directly. All linked repositories are hosted on GitHub and are subject to their respective licenses and GitHub's Terms of Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">User Conduct</h2>
        <p>When using the Service, you agree not to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Violate any applicable laws or regulations</li>
          <li>Attempt to bypass rate limits or access restrictions</li>
          <li>Use automated tools to scrape data excessively</li>
          <li>Submit spam, malicious packages, or misleading information</li>
          <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Service or servers</li>
          <li>Impersonate others or provide false information</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Contributing Packages</h2>
        <p>
          When submitting a package to the registry, you represent and warrant that:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>You have the right to submit the package information</li>
          <li>The package does not contain malicious code</li>
          <li>The package information is accurate and not misleading</li>
          <li>The package complies with its stated license</li>
          <li>You will maintain the accuracy of your submission</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We reserve the right to remove any package from the registry at our discretion, including but not limited to packages that violate these terms or are abandoned.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Intellectual Property</h2>
        
        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3">Zig Index</h3>
        <p>
          The Zig Index website, including its design, code, and documentation, is open source and available under the MIT License. You can find the source code on our <a href="https://github.com/AliSootworksArt/zig-index" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline">GitHub repository</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3 mt-4">Listed Packages</h3>
        <p>
          Each package listed on Zig Index is owned by its respective authors and is subject to its own license. Zig Index does not claim ownership of any listed package. Users should review individual package licenses before use.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3 mt-4">Zig Trademark</h3>
        <p>
          "Zig" and the Zig logo are trademarks of the Zig Software Foundation. Zig Index is a community project and is not officially affiliated with or endorsed by the Zig Software Foundation.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED. WE DO NOT WARRANT THAT:
