        <p>
          TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, ZIG INDEX AND ITS CONTRIBUTORS SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES ARISING FROM YOUR USE OF THE SERVICE OR ANY PACKAGES DISCOVERED THROUGH THE SERVICE.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>
          The Service contains links to third-party websites, including GitHub repositories. We are not responsible for the content, privacy policies, or practices of these third-party sites. We encourage you to review the terms and privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Modifications to Service</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue the Service at any time without notice. We may also update these Terms of Service from time to time. Continued use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the modified terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">GitHub API Usage</h2>
        <p>
          The Service uses the GitHub API to retrieve repository information. Your use of features that depend on the GitHub API is subject to <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/github-terms/github-terms-of-service" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline">GitHub's Terms of Service</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Community Guidelines</h2>
        <p>
          Zig Index is a community project. We expect all participants to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Be respectful and considerate in all interactions</li>
          <li>Provide constructive feedback</li>
          <li>Help maintain the quality of the registry</li>
          <li>Follow open source community best practices</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
